title: Official Court Transcript, 1 April 1946
n_arrangement: PRELIMINARY NOTES TO FRENCH TRANSCRIPTS: 1) The majority of the French transcripts are typewritten (with frequent manuscript notes). An occasional transcript session or portion of session is mimeographed. 2) It will be noted that the pagination is haphazard: sometimes pages are numbered session by session, sometimes merely identified according to each Court Reporter's "take". For purpose of this inventory, unnumbered pages were counted manually. This of course does not always establish what pages, if any, may be missing.

title: Official Court Transcript, 1 August 1946
n_arrangement: PRELIMINARY NOTES TO FRENCH TRANSCRIPTS: 1) The majority of the French transcripts are typewritten (with frequent manuscript notes). An occasional transcript session or portion of session is mimeographed. 2) It will be noted that the pagination is haphazard: sometimes pages are numbered session by session, sometimes merely identified according to each Court Reporter's "take". For purpose of this inventory, unnumbered pages were counted manually. This of course does not always establish what pages, if any, may be missing.

title: Official Court Transcript, 2 January 1946
n_arrangement: PRELIMINARY NOTES TO FRENCH TRANSCRIPTS: 1) The majority of the French transcripts are typewritten (with frequent manuscript notes). An occasional transcript session or portion of session is mimeographed. 2) It will be noted that the pagination is haphazard: sometimes pages are numbered session by session, sometimes merely identified according to each Court Reporter's "take". For purpose of this inventory, unnumbered pages were counted manually. This of course does not always establish what pages, if any, may be missing.

title: Official Court Transcript, 1 July 1946
n_arrangement: PRELIMINARY NOTES TO FRENCH TRANSCRIPTS: 1) The majority of the French transcripts are typewritten (with frequent manuscript notes). An occasional transcript session or portion of session is mimeographed. 2) It will be noted that the pagination is haphazard: sometimes pages are numbered session by session, sometimes merely identified according to each Court Reporter's "take". For purpose of this inventory, unnumbered pages were counted manually. This of course does not always establish what pages, if any, may be missing.

title: Official Court Transcript, 1 June 1946
n_arrangement: PRELIMINARY NOTES TO FRENCH TRANSCRIPTS: 1) The majority of the French transcripts are typewritten (with frequent manuscript notes). An occasional transcript session or portion of session is mimeographed. 2) It will be noted that the pagination is haphazard: sometimes pages are numbered session by session, sometimes merely identified according to each Court Reporter's "take". For purpose of this inventory, unnumbered pages were counted manually. This of course does not always establish what pages, if any, may be missing.

title: Official Court Transcript, 1 March 1946
n_arrangement: PRELIMINARY NOTES TO FRENCH TRANSCRIPTS: 1) The majority of the French transcripts are typewritten (with frequent manuscript notes). An occasional transcript session or portion of session is mimeographed. 2) It will be noted that the pagination is haphazard: sometimes pages are numbered session by session, sometimes merely identified according to each Court Reporter's "take". For purpose of this inventory, unnumbered pages were counted manually. This of course does not always establish what pages, if any, may be missing.
